# Add Painless Vital Sign Orders

This plan details the changes required to implement automatic "check vital sign" (CVS) medical orders after a painless labor medication prescription.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend ([his_client.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py))
#### [MODIFY] his_client.py(file:///c:/Users/A03772/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py)
- Implement a new method `prescribe_painless_vitals(patient_data)`:
  - Prescribe two orders:
    1. `XTR00403` (Check vital signs Q30min...)
    2. `XTR00024` (@Check vital signs)
  - Use the two-step IpoC151 process (`ProcessBASOTGP` then `Save`).
  - Frequency for both: `ASORDER`.

### Backend ([app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/app.py))
#### [MODIFY] app.py(file:///c:/Users/A03772/AutoPrescribe_ver2/app.py)
- In the [prescribe](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/app.py#37-79) route, after a successful `PAINLESS` prescription:
  - Call `client.prescribe_painless_vitals(patient_data)`.
  - Ensure any errors in this step are logged but don't prevent the PDF from being returned.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run simulation of painless prescription and verify subsequent calls to IpoC151/Save for the two TR codes.

### Manual Verification
1. Prescribe a "Painless Labor" package from the UI.
2. Confirm medication PDF is downloaded.
3. Check the "Orders" section in the HIS system (simulation/pcap comparison) to ensure `XTR00403` and `XTR00024` were submitted.
